1. INTELLECTUAL PRIORITY DECLARATION
================================================================================

This repository implements the core algorithmic architecture of "The Eriksson 
Programme" — a constructive proof framework for the Yang-Mills Existence and 
Mass Gap problem (Clay Mathematics Institute Millennium Problem #4).

The unique methodological pipeline ("architectural signature") of this 
programme is:

  Step 1: Balaban Renormalization Group (RG) Bridge
          Rigorous lattice-to-continuum limit via Balaban's 29 lemmas
  
  Step 2: Kotecký-Preiss Polymer Expansion
          Convergence validation of cluster expansions with explicit 
          eta-bounds
  
  Step 3: Osterwalder-Schrader Axiom Verification
          Mechanical audit of OS reflection positivity
          (condition OS1: O(eta^2 log eta^{-1}))
  
  Step 4: Wightman Reconstruction
          Passage from Euclidean to Minkowski QFT with mass gap Delta > 0

This specific four-step pipeline, combined with the "mechanical lemma-audit" 
verification methodology, constitutes the original intellectual contribution 
of Lluis Eriksson.

